    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-25T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="407"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79690/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Farrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-25T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 25, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>128. Department’s 95, May 19;<note n="10" xml:id="d407fn10">Not printed.</note>
                    and Legation’s 126 [<hi rend="italic">127</hi>], July [<hi rend="italic"
                        >June</hi>] 22. Basra customs authorities demanding cash payment of duty on
                    Pan American imports for improving Basra airport despite local guarantees of
                    payment of [<hi rend="italic">as?</hi>] Pan American does not <pb facs="0360"
                        n="348" xml:id="pg_348"/> acquire customs exemption as an agency of the
                    United States Government. Legation will appreciate indication of present status
                    of negotiations regarding Pan American in Iraq.</p>
                <p>Sent to Department repeated to Cairo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Farrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
